# HubSpot: submitting a form via API

This project posts demo requests to HubSpot using the **public Forms v3 integration** endpoint (no private app token required for this flow).

## Endpoint

```http
POST https://api.hsforms.com/submissions/v3/integration/submit/{portalId}/{formGuid}
Content-Type: application/json
```

- **`portalId`**: HubSpot account (Hub) ID ‚Äî numeric, same as in `https://app.hubspot.com/.../{portalId}/...`.
- **`formGuid`**: The form‚Äôs GUID (UUID) from Marketing ‚Üí Forms ‚Üí form settings / embed.

Override in this repo via env (defaults are in `src/app/api/hubspot/demo/route.ts`):

- `HUBSPOT_PORTAL_ID`
- `HUBSPOT_DEMO_FORM_GUID`

## Request body

HubSpot expects JSON with at least:

- **`fields`**: array of `{ "name": "<internal field name>", "value": "<string>" }`.
  - Each **`name`** must match the **internal name** of a field on that exact form (not the label). In HubSpot: open the form ‚Üí select a field ‚Üí **Internal name** / property mapping.
  - If the form marks a field as required in HubSpot, you must include it or the API returns **400** (e.g. missing `lastname`, `phone`).
- **`context`** (recommended): `{ "pageUri": "<url>", "pageName": "<label>" }` for attribution.
- **`context.hutk`** (optional): visitor token from the `hubspotutk` cookie when the tracking script is present ‚Äî helps merge sessions in HubSpot.

Example shape:

```json
{
  "fields": [
    { "name": "firstname", "value": "Jane" },
    { "name": "lastname", "value": "Doe" },
    { "name": "email", "value": "jane@example.com" },
    { "name": "phone", "value": "+52..." },
    { "name": "company", "value": "Acme" }
  ],
  "context": {
    "pageUri": "https://example.com/schedule-demo/",
    "pageName": "Solicitar Demo ‚Äî Nuvigant",
    "hutk": "optional-cookie-value"
  }
}
```

## Responses and errors

- **2xx**: submission accepted.
- **4xx**: invalid payload ‚Äî read the JSON body; common cases are wrong **`fields[].name`** (typo vs form) or **required fields missing**. Fix the mapping or add fields in code to match the live HubSpot form.
- This app‚Äôs route maps non-success HubSpot responses to **502** for the browser but logs **`[hubspot demo]`** with status and body in the server log for debugging.

## Implementation in this repo

| Piece | Role |
|--------|------|
| `POST /api/hubspot/demo` | Validates JSON from the site, maps Spanish keys to HubSpot **`fields`**, calls `api.hsforms.com`. |
| `src/components/ScheduleDemoForm.tsx` | Client form; sends `nombre` ‚Üí `firstname`, `apellidos` ‚Üí `lastname`, plus `email`, `telefono` ‚Üí `phone`, optional `empresa` ‚Üí `company`, optional `mensaje` ‚Üí `message`, plus `pageUri` and optional `hutk`. |

**`FIELD_MAP`** in the route maps our optional/custom keys to HubSpot internal names. If you add or rename properties on the HubSpot form, update **`FIELD_MAP`** and/or the explicit `firstname` / `lastname` handling to stay in sync.

